mainText: “A girl’s got to use what she’s given<break time=".3s"/> and I’m not going to make a guy drool the way a Britney video does.<break time=".6s"/> So I take it to extremes. I don’t say I dress sexily on stage - what I do is so extreme. It’s meant to make guys think:<break time=".3s"/> ‘I don’t know if this is sexy or just weird.”<break time="1s"/> Lady Gaga

“Individual heterosexual women, came to the movement from relationships where, men were cruel, unkind, violent, unfaithful.<break time=".6s"/> Many of these men, were radical thinkers who participated in movements for social justice, speaking out on behalf of the workers, the poor, speaking out on behalf of racial justice.<break time=".6s"/> However, when it came to the issue of gender, they were as sexist as their conservative cohorts.”<break time="1s"/> this was said by, bell hooks
